<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment">
	A <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> is a type of 
	<express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.effectivity_context_assignment"/> 
	that implements the ARM concept of
	<express_ref linkend="Specification_control:arm:Specification_control_arm.Specification_category_breakdown_influence"/>.
	A <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> assigns an <express_ref linkend="effectivity_application:mim:Effectivity_application_mim.applied_effectivity_assignment"/> 
	specifying the 
	<express_ref linkend="Effectivity_application:mim:Effectivity_application_mim.effectivity_item">effectivity_items</express_ref> 
	that impact the design of a solution for a 
	<express_ref linkend="Specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_item"/>. 

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  Attribute: items 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.items"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.items">

the set of items for which the <express_ref linkend="effectivity_application:mim:Effectivity_application_mim.applied_effectivity_assignment"/> identifies a design impact.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  Where: WR1 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR1"/>



  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR1">

The <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> shall have a role with a name of 'class usage influence'.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  Where: WR2 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR2"/>



  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR2">

The <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> shall only have instances of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> in its set of items which reference as "frame of reference" a <express_ref linkend="application_context_schema:ir_express:application_context_schema.product_definition_context"/> with name 'conceptual definition'.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  Where: WR3 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR3"/>



  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR3">

The <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> shall reference an <express_ref linkend="effectivity_application:mim:Effectivity_application_mim.applied_effectivity_assignment"/> with an "assigned effectivity" which is not of an effectivity subtype and which has an id of 'class usage' and which has only <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage"/> objects in the set of items. 

</ext_description>

	

