	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: breakdown_element_requires_product_definition 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.breakdown_element_requires_product_definition"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.breakdown_element_requires_product_definition">

The <b>breakdown_element_requires_product_definition</b> rule constrains any instance of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_formation"/> that represents a version of a functional element or of a physical element to have at least a corresponding definition.

</ext_description>

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.breakdown_element_requires_product_definition.wr:WR1">

Any <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_formation"/> that represents a version of a function element shall be referred by at least one "product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'functional definition'.

</ext_description>

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.breakdown_element_requires_product_definition.wr:WR2">

Any <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_formation"/> that represents a version of a physical element shall be referred by at least one "product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'conceptual definition'.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association">

<p>The <b>restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association</b> rule constrains any instance of 
<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/> 
of type 'design constraint association' to have:</p>

<ul>

			<li>a 
			<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.relating_product_definition"/> 
			whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition';
			</li>

			<li>a 
			<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.related_product_definition"/>  
			whose frame of reference name is 'alternative definition' , 'functional definition' or 'conceptual definition'.</li>

</ul>

	</ext_description>

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association.wr:WR1">

<p>There shall not be any instance of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/> of type 'design constraint association' that does not have:</p>

<ul>

			<li>a 
			<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.relating_product_definition"/> 
			whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition', or,</li>

			<li>a 
			<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship.related_product_definition"/>  
			whose frame of reference name is 'alternative definition' , 'functional definition' or 'conceptual definition'.</li>

		</ul>

	</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category">

The <b>constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category</b> rule constrains any instance of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition', to be a definition of a product of category 'requirement'.

</ext_description>

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category.wr:WR1">

There shall not be any instance of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition' and which is not a definition of a product of category 'requirement'.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: design_constraint_requires_product_definition 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.design_constraint_requires_product_definition"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.design_constraint_requires_product_definition">

The <b>design_constraint_requires_product_definition</b> rule constrains any instance of 
<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_formation"/> of a product of category 'requirement' to have at least a corresponding definition.

</ext_description>
<!-- WR1 -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.design_constraint_requires_product_definition.wr:WR1">
	Any <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_formation"/> 
	of a product of category 'requirement'  shall be referred by at least one 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> 
	whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition'.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint">
	<p>The <b>restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint</b> constrains any instance of 
	<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_design"/> 
	that has a name 'design constraint usage' 
	to refer with its design attribute to a 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> 
	whose 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition.frame_of_reference"/>
	name is 'design constraint definition'.</p>

<note>This ensures that use <express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_design"/> to represent a "Design constraint context association" is correct.</note>

	</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint  Where: WR1 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint.wr:WR1"/>



  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of 
<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_design"/> 
that has a name 'design constraint usage',
that does not refer with its design attribute to a 
<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> 
whose 
<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition.frame_of_reference"/> 
name is 'design constraint definition'.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association">
	The <b>restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association</b> constrains any instance of 
	<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_design"/> 
	that has a name 'functionality'
	to refer with its design attribute to a 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> 
	whose 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition.frame_of_reference"/> 
	name is 'functional definition'.
<p> It also constrains any instance of 
	<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_design"/> 
	that has a name 'realization'
	to refer with its design attribute to a 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> 
	whose 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition.frame_of_reference"/> 
	name is 'conceptual definition'.
</p>
<p>In both cases, the 
	<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_item.item_concept"/> 
	indirectly referred to, shall be a 
	<express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_class"/>.

</p>

	</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association  Where: WR1 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR1"/>



  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR1">

	There shall not be any instance of 
	<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_design"/> 
	that has a name 'functionality'
	that does not refer with its design attribute to a 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> 
	whose 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition.frame_of_reference"/>
	name is 'functional definition'.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association  Where: WR2 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR2"/>



  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR2">

	There shall not be any instance of 
	<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_design"/> 
	that has a name 'realization'
	that does not refer with its design attribute to a 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> 
	whose 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition.frame_of_reference"/>
	name is 'conceptual definition'.

</ext_description>

	<!-- 

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association  Where: WR3 

   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR3"/>



  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

  -->

	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR3">

	There shall not be any instance of 
	<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_design"/> 
	that has a name 'realization' or 'functionality', 
	that does not indirectly refer to an 
	<express_ref linkend="configuration_management_schema:ir_express:configuration_management_schema.configuration_item.item_concept"/> 
	of type 
	<express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_class"/>.

</ext_description>

